Dear OCT 2001 Contributor:

We are happy to inform you that your paper with title:

"On Component-Based Communication Systems for Cluster of Workstations"

has been accepted for inclusion in the 2001 International Workshop on
Object and Component Technologies for Cluster Computing.  All of the 
reviews that were written concerning your paper have been attached
To assist you in preparing the final camera-ready copy. Please follow the
referee's comments as much as possible. 

The final version of your paper is due by January 24, 2001. This paper should
be not more than 8 (eight) pages of double column text using single spaced
10 point size type on 8.5 x 11 inch pages (U. S. letter paper), as per IEEE
manuscript guidelines. Exact IEEE instrcutions can be accessed from:

http://www.computer.org/cspress/instruct.htm
ftp://ftp.computer.org/pub/outgoing/cspress/proceedings/IEEE_CS_Latex.zip

Further instructions will be sent to you soon by the proceedings editor.

We look forward to your participation in OCT 2001. Information about 
registration, accommodation, etc., will soon be available on the main
conference WWW page, http://www.ccgrid.org.

Sincerely,


Rajeev Raje and Barrett Bryant
OCT 2001 Workshop Chairs
