COMMENTS TO AUTHOR:  (Please use additional sheet(s) if necessary)

Overall, this is a good preliminary paper.  However, there are many
grammar mistakes that distract from the points you are trying to make.

Some comments/questions:

  - a better example (with a little more detail) of how target users
    use your tools would be helpful

  - you specify a methodology and give an example of how your system
    works ... but it is unclear how beneficial or compelling it would
    be to end users (e.g., "inflated interfaces" seems to suggest
    that programmers will need to learn a large number of complicated
    APIs in order to use your system)

  - it appears the generated runtimes are statically determined and
    built; can the runtime system adapt to faster communication
    channels or topologies? (i.e., how flexible is the generated
    runtime system to further optimizations?)
