COMMENTS TO AUTHOR:  (Please use additional sheet(s) if necessary)

This paper provides an interesting introduction to ambitious work 
needed to aid in the construction of portable, parallel software.
Though the work is not complete, it presents useful ideas
on multi-platform parallel programming, and is worthy of
publication.

Much of the English grammar is "rough" and needs to be improved.

It isn't too difficult to follow the "flow" of the paper, but
it definitely needs proof-reading and revision.

The EPOS project is mentioned over and over again, but not once
(that I could see), is the acronym spelled out. 

Overall, I think the theme of this paper is valuable, and that
it will make a great contribution to the Proceedings once
the paper is proof-read and revised.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

